1.00	Brad_Johnson_(American_football_player)	Brad Johnson (American football)	James Bradley "Brad" Johnson (born September 13, 1968) is a former American football quarterback who played for seventeen seasons in the National Football League. After playing college football for the Florida State Seminoles, he was drafted by the Minnesota Vikings in the ninth round of the 1992 NFL Draft. He spent seven seasons with the Vikings and two seasons with the Washington Redskins before becoming the starting quarterback of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers in 2001. He led the Buccaneers to Super Bowl XXXVII where they were victorious against the Oakland Raiders. He played for the Buccaneers for four seasons from 2001 to 2004, the Minnesota Vikings for two more seasons from 2005 to 2006, and the Dallas Cowboys for two seasons from 2007 to 2008.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/BradJohnson.jpg/220px-BradJohnson.jpg
